OL,4,CSouth America's drought-hit Parana
OL,5,Criver at 77-year low
OL,6, The water levels of the Parana river,
OL,7, the second-longest in South America
OL,8, after the Amazon, are at their lowest
OL,9, since 1944.
OL,11,FThe river is key to commercial shipping
OL,12,Fand fishing but also provides 40
OL,13,Fmillion people with drinking water.
OL,15,FA drought in the region means water
OL,16,Flevels have dipped so low that fishers'
OL,17,Flivelihoods are at risk.
OL,19,FEnvironmentalists fear that the drought
OL,20,Fhas been made more severe by
OL,21,Fdeforestation and climate change.
